collections.name: Hime no Tatakai
collections.description: Hime no Tatakai, or "The Princess's Battle," by Yuki explores the rarely told stories of onna-bugeisha (female samurai) who balanced elegance and strength as they defied tradition to take up arms. Set against dynamic, shifting backdrops of swirling red suns and weathered textures, these 94 unique works—Yuki’s largest collection yet—capture the crossroads of beauty and defiance, blending fierce determination with the grace of martial combat. Original art created using traditional ink wash and mixed media on wood, these pieces were submitted to Orangehare.io and adapted for use as digital collectibles.

collections.name: Cosmic Eyes
collections.description:
Cosmic Eyes: A Portal to Infinite Creativity

Cosmic Eyes is a limited collection of 45 vibrant, surreal NFTs that merge bold graffiti-inspired aesthetics with abstract storytelling. Each piece is a unique journey into the cosmos of human imagination, featuring exaggerated characters, chaotic symbols, and whimsical elements that spark curiosity and wonder.

More than just art, Cosmic Eyes represents a gateway to explore the universe within — a celebration of individuality, creativity, and perception. Each "eye" in the collection symbolizes vision, reminding us that every viewer brings their perspective to the artwork.

Owning a Cosmic Eye is more than acquiring a digital asset; it’s joining an exclusive community of visionaries who embrace creativity and the transformative power of art. Holders will gain access to future airdrops, creative collaborations, and unique experiences curated to inspire and connect.

Unlock your vision with Cosmic Eyes. See beyond the ordinary.

collections.name: Hide Me In Shadows
collections.description:
OSHO said that "creativity is the greatest rebellion in existence."

I’d like to think of my work as a rebellion against how the naked body has been portrayed in media and art. I believe the nude form is a powerful tool to challenge stigmas, promote sexual education, and shape the future of body rights.

This collection uses chiaroscuro, strong contrasts of light and dark to highlight the natural beauty of the nude form while concealing the model’s identity, focusing on on the art itself.

Minted on [Foundation](https://foundation.app/collection/HideMeInShadows)

collections.name: Nature and I
collections.description:
It’s in the time we spend in nature, where we find truth.

Nature teaches us that we’re all from the same earth, intertwined, complex, and extraordinarily beautiful when we peek deeper.

In the past years, I’ve enjoyed capturing the relationship between nature and the nude form, using plants, leaves, and flowers from my garden. What struck me the most is how easy the two subjects complemented each other, effortlessly fabricating a beautiful reality.

collections.name: ShowFuku
collections.description:
Title: Japanese Gods and Yokai – A Pop Art Collection

“Experience the charm of Japan’s divine and mythical world through vibrant, playful art!”

Description:

This unique NFT collection brings Japan’s rich spiritual and mythical heritage to life with a modern, pop art twist.
	•	The Seven Lucky Gods (Shichifukujin): Celebrate prosperity, happiness, and good fortune with colorful depictions of Japan’s beloved deities.
	•	The Eight Million Gods (Yaoyorozu no Kami): Explore the endless diversity of Japan’s spiritual world, where gods reside in every aspect of nature and daily life.
	•	Japanese Yokai (Mythical Creatures): From mischievous spirits to legendary beasts, meet the fascinating characters that have captured imaginations for centuries.

Each artwork is a playful reimagining of traditional Japanese motifs, designed to be both culturally meaningful and accessible to a global audience.

Why Collect?
	•	Bring the energy and charm of Japan’s divine world into your digital collection.

collections.name: Teleo
collections.description:
Teléo
Teléo is an ancient guardian from a world intertwined with magic and technology. He is a being tasked with preserving knowledge of the past and understanding future technology. 
The television antennas extend his senses, allowing him to capture signals and stories from far away, while his blue eyes symbolize his ability to see through to the truth.

One day, Teléo appears in a forgotten village, showing its residents their lost history through the television screen. At times raging with passion and at others acting like a soldier, he puts his all into performing and suggests ways to resolve the chaos caused by modern technology threatening the village. Thanks to his whimsical appearance and unexpected wisdom, the villagers initially find him strange, but they ultimately regain peace with his help. This story could become a warm and humorous adventure tale exploring how technology and tradition, past and future, can coexist.

Love, joy, sadness, compassion and many others can be conveyed without saying a single word.
Despite the diversity of thought inside each individual mind, despite the diversity of a human worldview, it is essential for the author to fit his main message to the spectator in one painted picture.
This is the core value of any artwork- everyone may see the same picture in front of them, but it will resonate within us in different ways!
Each painting makes You think about the eternal and charges a spectator with rich energy in its own way. 
So, when You look at these paintings, the only one is responding, which is closer to Your inner world.

Now you can buy the eternity!
